01:21:39,192 --> 01:21:42,182
My father says there once
was a good man in you.

972
01:21:43,361 --> 01:21:45,482
I wasn't aware he departed.

973
01:21:45,572 --> 01:21:47,981
You do quite a lot for the people here.

974
01:21:48,452 --> 01:21:52,620
But we both know, your good works
are mitigated by your evil deeds.

975
01:21:52,665 --> 01:21:53,981
We do?

976
01:21:54,335 --> 01:21:57,463
You profit from the illegal
addictions of others...

977
01:21:57,547 --> 01:22:01,040
...their weakness and sloth
and libidinous behavior...

978
01:22:02,093 --> 01:22:04,283
...but you can free yourself of that.

979
01:22:04,556 --> 01:22:06,250
And I don't want to.

980
01:22:06,558 --> 01:22:08,218
Of course you do.

981
01:22:09,855 --> 01:22:12,313
Miss Figgis, you're a lovely woman...

982
01:22:12,482 --> 01:22:14,502
...and your story is amazing.

983
01:22:14,537 --> 01:22:17,791
I'm not surprised the flock's
up threefold since you started here.

984
01:22:17,826 --> 01:22:19,497
More like 5 times.

985
01:22:20,408 --> 01:22:24,008
More booze has been drunk
in the last 10 years than ever before...

986
01:22:24,043 --> 01:22:26,240
...because people don't
wanna be told they can't do it.

987
01:22:26,624 --> 01:22:29,190
The same could be said of fornication.

988
01:22:29,672 --> 01:22:33,706
People want it, but don't
wanna be told they can't have it.

989
01:22:33,741 --> 01:22:35,305
Why should they?

990
01:22:35,719 --> 01:22:36,935
I'm sorry?

991
01:22:36,970 --> 01:22:39,702
If people want to fornicate,
I see no reason to stop them.

992
01:22:39,724 --> 01:22:43,694
And if they wish to lie down with animals?
Do they?

993
01:22:44,274 --> 01:22:45,697
I'm sorry?

994
01:22:45,732 --> 01:22:48,643
Do people wish to lie down with animals?
Some do.

995
01:22:48,743 --> 01:22:51,299
And their sickness will spread
if you have your way.

996
01:22:51,383 --> 01:22:54,144
Forgive me. I see no correlation between
alcohol and lyin' down with animals.

997
01:22:54,179 --> 01:22:56,883
There's a correlation across all sin.

998
01:22:56,918 --> 01:23:02,212
It's all against the wishes of God,
therefore all equally offensive.

999
01:23:03,005 --> 01:23:06,617
Let me apologize. I think we
got off on the wrong foot here.

1000
01:23:06,826 --> 01:23:09,558
I'm just here to ask you if
you would be amenable...

1001
01:23:09,560 --> 01:23:13,258
to omitting the Casino issue
from your sermons...

1002
01:23:13,266 --> 01:23:16,979
...and in exchange,
we're gonna bring a business here.

1003
01:23:17,063 --> 01:23:18,573
Business will create jobs...

1004
01:23:18,608 --> 01:23:21,104
...which will reduce the
sinfulness that comes with...

1005
01:23:21,105 --> 01:23:23,804
...poverty and idle hands.

1006
01:23:24,364 --> 01:23:26,399
We'd be willing to
contribute to the church.

1007
01:23:26,434 --> 01:23:29,280
No, we'd be willing to
build a few churches.

1008
01:23:35,546 --> 01:23:39,474
If God rewrites the Bible to
cast gambling as virtuous...

1009
01:23:39,509 --> 01:23:42,236
...I will refrain from
speaking against it.

1010
01:23:42,639 --> 01:23:48,746
But until then, we don't get to
pick our sins, Mr. Coughlin.

1011
01:23:53,985 --> 01:23:55,766
I can't do it.

1012
01:23:56,364 --> 01:24:00,272
What? It's gonna fuck up the whole deal.
What do you mean, you can't do it?

1013
01:24:00,372 --> 01:24:03,325
I know. No one touches her.

1014
01:24:05,123 --> 01:24:06,846
That's a mistake.

1015
01:24:08,295 --> 01:24:10,067
No shit.

1016
01:24:23,730 --> 01:24:27,324
Can we get you anything?
No, we're ok, thanks.

1017
01:24:27,859 --> 01:24:31,863
We know you men are busy and
we don't want to waste your time.

1018
01:24:32,073 --> 01:24:35,438
We are not going to invest
in the casino at the Ritz.

1019
01:24:38,958 --> 01:24:41,845
Are you... sure about that?
I'm afraid so.

1020
01:24:41,880 --> 01:24:43,919
The publicity is too much.

1021
01:24:43,954 --> 01:24:46,202
One woman preachin' in a fuckin' tent?

1022
01:24:46,237 --> 01:24:50,765
Yes, because the casino would
represent only 2% of our total holdings...

1023
01:24:50,849 --> 01:24:56,172
...and we can't appear to be a
company of Irish and Italian Catholics...

1024
01:24:56,207 --> 01:24:59,515
...turning white
Protestant girls into drug addicts.

1025
01:25:00,317 --> 01:25:03,356
People I work for are gonna
be very upset about this.

1026
01:25:03,448 --> 01:25:06,075
We aren't men to be muscled or conned.

1027
01:25:06,159 --> 01:25:09,701
We are an institution.
We can't be bribed or bullied...

1028
01:25:09,704 --> 01:25:14,220
...because I simply represent the
vested interest of a board of governors.

1029
01:25:14,255 --> 01:25:17,264
We are the landed, white
gentry in this country...

1030
01:25:17,299 --> 01:25:21,888
...and we have no plans to
carve off a strip of this country...

1031
01:25:21,972 --> 01:25:25,384
...which we have gone to
great pains to break and colonize...

1032
01:25:25,419 --> 01:25:30,160
...and hand it over to Catholics,
Jews, darkies or dagos.

1033
01:25:32,024 --> 01:25:35,056
It's just a bigger, better racket,
that's all...

1034
01:25:35,091 --> 01:25:38,433
...keepin' the money in your hands
and out of the hands of people like us.

1035
01:25:41,620 --> 01:25:43,871
All those people...

1036
01:25:43,955 --> 01:25:49,848
...the Negro, on whose back you went
to great pains to break this country...

1037
01:25:49,883 --> 01:25:51,999
...and the immigrants who
came over here with nothin'...

1038
01:25:52,034 --> 01:25:53,927
...and worked their fingers
to the fuckin' bone...

1039
01:25:54,011 --> 01:25:58,620
...all believed it when you told
them they could get ahead...

1040
01:25:58,655 --> 01:26:02,146
...and one day, and I may not live
to see it, they're gonna figure it out.

1041
01:26:02,230 --> 01:26:05,299
But I tell you what,
I'd hate to fuckin' be you.

1042
01:26:05,526 --> 01:26:10,191
Standin' between those people
and what they deserve.

1043
01:26:12,575 --> 01:26:15,185
Good luck to you, prick!

1044
01:26:18,498 --> 01:26:20,539
Would have been a hell of a casino.

1045
01:26:21,170 --> 01:26:25,710
You'll get another chance.
Things swing back around.

1046
01:26:26,260 --> 01:26:27,634
Not all things.

1047
01:26:28,635 --> 01:26:31,927
They announced it on the radio,
just when we got back.

1048
01:26:34,018 --> 01:26:37,612
President-Elect Roosevelt promised
to sign the Cullen-Harrison Act...

1049
01:26:37,647 --> 01:26:42,167
...the minute he was elected,
effectively ending Prohibition.

1050
01:27:20,035 --> 01:27:22,705
Hello, Ms. Figgis!
Mr. Coughlin.

1051
01:27:22,740 --> 01:27:26,017
May I? Yeah.
Just for a minute? Please sit.

1052
01:27:27,961 --> 01:27:29,748
You're lookin' very well.

1053
01:27:30,088 --> 01:27:34,001
I see, you're not wearin' white.

1054
01:27:34,678 --> 01:27:36,701
It's almost white.

1055
01:27:37,598 --> 01:27:39,346
Would you like a menu?
Thank you very much.

1056
01:27:39,381 --> 01:27:40,896
Can I get a cup of coffee, please?

1057
01:27:44,065 --> 01:27:45,400
Thank you.

1058
01:27:52,116 --> 01:27:54,800
Why does my father hate you so much?

1059
01:27:57,291 --> 01:28:00,920
I'm a crook. He's the Chief of Police.

1060
01:28:00,955 --> 01:28:02,431
That's how it goes, I guess.

1061
01:28:02,589 --> 01:28:07,170
No, he liked you.
He said you were the mayor of Ybor.

1062
01:28:07,803 --> 01:28:09,377
Is that what he said?
Mm-hmm.

1063
01:28:13,811 --> 01:28:15,389
What did you do...

1064
01:28:18,064 --> 01:28:19,828
...to him?

1065
01:28:32,290 --> 01:28:34,298
We had photographs.

1066
01:28:39,343 --> 01:28:41,090
And you showed them to him.

1067
01:28:41,385 --> 01:28:42,936
I showed him two.

1068
01:28:43,512 --> 01:28:45,655
How many did you have?

1069
01:28:46,560 --> 01:28:47,938
All of them.

1070
01:28:53,525 --> 01:28:55,635
We're all going to hell.

1071
01:28:57,198 --> 01:28:59,116
I don't think you're going to hell.

1072
01:28:59,200 --> 01:29:01,376
You know what I learned...

1073
01:29:01,996 --> 01:29:06,838
...as I've been thrusting
my soul out to God?

1074
01:29:06,873 --> 01:29:08,005
What?

1075
01:29:09,673 --> 01:29:14,382
This is heaven...right here.

1076
01:29:15,512 --> 01:29:17,186
We're in it now.

1077
01:29:17,431 --> 01:29:19,477
Then how come it looks like hell?

1078
01:29:19,641 --> 01:29:21,942
Because we fucked it all up.

1079
01:29:30,199 --> 01:29:32,969
After my trials...

1080
01:29:36,747 --> 01:29:39,042
...I slept in the bed of my childhood.

1081
01:29:43,215 --> 01:29:45,466
I felt certain again.

1082
01:29:47,136 --> 01:29:48,385
I missed that.

1083
01:29:54,313 --> 01:29:56,396
I don't know if there is a God...

1084
01:30:00,609 --> 01:30:02,531
...but I hope there is...

1085
01:30:05,615 --> 01:30:07,702
...and I hope he's kind.

1086
01:30:10,750 --> 01:30:12,710
Wouldn't that be swell?

1087
01:30:16,757 --> 01:30:18,343
Yes, it would be.

1088
01:30:25,308 --> 01:30:28,020
You seem not to despair.
Do you have a secret?

1089
01:30:28,104 --> 01:30:30,234
No, no secrets.

1090
01:30:31,608 --> 01:30:35,998
I have my wife. That's enough.

1091
01:30:37,031 --> 01:30:39,082
But what if you lose her?

1092
01:30:44,248 --> 01:30:45,817
What are you going to do now?

1093
01:30:46,418 --> 01:30:51,144
What do you mean?
You stopped me, stopped the casino...

1094
01:30:51,425 --> 01:30:52,802
...law couldn't do it...

1095
01:30:52,886 --> 01:30:57,472
...the people couldn't do it.
The Klan couldn't do it. You did it.

1096
01:30:57,556 --> 01:31:01,353
I didn't get rid of alchohol.
No, that was too big.

1097
01:31:01,388 --> 01:31:04,858
But you stopped gambling and before
you came along it was a lock.

1098
01:31:05,110 --> 01:31:08,284
I did do that, didn't I?
Yes, you did.

1099
01:31:11,242 --> 01:31:13,200
What's your father gonna do?

1100
01:31:14,746 --> 01:31:16,748
Sit in his chair, I guess...

1101
01:31:17,497 --> 01:31:19,188
...blind with rage that...

1102
01:31:19,288 --> 01:31:23,688
...men touched his daughter
the way he used to touch his wife...

1103
01:31:23,825 --> 01:31:25,300
...and worse.

1104
01:31:31,435 --> 01:31:35,959
He goes around the house
whispering one word over and over.

1105
01:31:36,441 --> 01:31:37,775
What word?

1106
01:31:38,776 --> 01:31:40,579
Repent.

1107
01:31:44,075 --> 01:31:46,824
Repent, repent.

1108
01:31:49,790 --> 01:31:52,677
Give him some time.
Maybe he'll come out of it.

1109
01:32:27,630 --> 01:32:30,381
We heard from Boston.
All three trucks made it up there fine.

1110
01:32:30,465 --> 01:32:32,924
Same payoffs as last week.
So, there's no problem.

1111
01:32:32,959 --> 01:32:34,057
Very good.

1112
01:32:34,178 --> 01:32:36,966
And Loretta Figgis cut
her own throat yesterday.

1113
01:32:38,475 --> 01:32:39,933
What?

1114
01:32:40,185 --> 01:32:42,980
Yeah, she did it at home
in the Chief's bed, they say.

1115
01:32:44,106 --> 01:32:45,669
You gotta give it to her...

1116
01:32:46,946 --> 01:32:49,466
...she's got moxie!
I couldn't do that.

1117
01:32:50,322 --> 01:32:53,011
You know, I guess
some things are meant to be.

1118
01:32:53,046 --> 01:32:56,530
She could have done it 3 months earlier
and done us all a fuckin' favor.

1119
01:32:57,583 --> 01:32:59,752
Well, too late.

1120
01:33:11,956 --> 01:33:15,492
<i>Death of a Madonna</i>
You blame yourself?

1121
01:33:16,354 --> 01:33:19,486
She went out West as
so many other girls do...

1122
01:33:19,570 --> 01:33:21,024
...and she was preyed upon.

1123
01:33:21,360 --> 01:33:22,871
Not by you.

1124
01:33:22,906 --> 01:33:24,324
Well, by men like me...

1125
01:33:24,409 --> 01:33:29,163
...to get the booze,
to get the girls, get the drugs...

1126
01:33:29,247 --> 01:33:31,377
...one hand washes the other.

1127
01:33:31,870 --> 01:33:37,341
You don't need it, mi amigo,
We are not our brother's keeper.

1128
01:33:37,425 --> 01:33:40,637
In fact it is an insult to
our brother to believe we are.

1129
01:33:40,721 --> 01:33:42,387
Look at these people.

1130
01:33:43,472 --> 01:33:47,105
If this man dies of, say drunkenness...

1131
01:33:47,185 --> 01:33:48,990
...is it our fault?

1132
01:33:52,484 --> 01:33:54,639
When did you take this picture?

1133
01:33:55,656 --> 01:33:57,331
A month ago.

1134
01:33:58,159 --> 01:33:59,722
Are you sure?

1135
01:34:01,747 --> 01:34:06,853
I took this picture myself.
A month and three days ago. Why?

1136
01:34:08,132 --> 01:34:11,069
Because that woman died in 1927.

1137
01:34:53,385 --> 01:34:56,405
There's never been
anyone like you in my life.

1138
01:34:58,651 --> 01:35:01,194
One day I'm going to
be good enough for you.

1139
01:35:03,697 --> 01:35:06,296
You sure it's her?
You tell me.

1140
01:35:07,246 --> 01:35:09,932
You told Graciela?
Of course I told her.

1141
01:35:11,250 --> 01:35:13,086
Jesus Christ.

1142
01:35:13,585 --> 01:35:15,308
What you wouldn't tell your woman?

1143
01:35:15,424 --> 01:35:18,968
No, I don't tell them shit
but you're more of a nance than me.

1144
01:35:19,052 --> 01:35:21,080
What'd you say?
Look, sorry, hon...

1145
01:35:21,090 --> 01:35:22,980
...that girl I was bent out of shape
over for years...

1146
01:35:22,990 --> 01:35:25,180
...she's not dead. She's in Miami.

1147
01:35:25,184 --> 01:35:27,563
Don't make a big
fuckin' thing out of it.

1148
01:35:35,072 --> 01:35:36,198
When you go home?

1149
01:35:36,699 --> 01:35:38,039
Going where?
What do you mean where?

1150
01:35:38,050 --> 01:35:40,939
You found out this girl you used
to be bugs for is 200 miles away.

1151
01:35:41,039 --> 01:35:42,893
When you goin'?

1152
01:35:47,504 --> 01:35:52,352
I'm goin' to go after this thing with Maso.
Good. Give you something to live for.

1153
01:35:53,051 --> 01:35:54,144
What does that mean?

1154
01:35:54,179 --> 01:35:57,557
Him and his guys are takin' over
half the train to get down here.

1155
01:35:59,267 --> 01:36:01,138
That's a big fucking entourage!

1156
01:36:02,106 --> 01:36:04,525
Ah, bullshit,
I ain't worried about it.

1157
01:36:04,609 --> 01:36:06,511
There's no percentage in killin' us.

1158
01:36:07,277 --> 01:36:11,871
We do $ 11.5 million a year from
rum alone in this fuckin' cop town.

1159
01:36:12,296 --> 01:36:13,459
What's he gonna kill us for?

1160
01:36:13,460 --> 01:36:16,959
All we do is send him bags of money
up to his mansion in fuckin' Mahatts.

1161
01:36:17,059 --> 01:36:19,004
I don't like the signs.
What fuckin' signs?

1162
01:36:19,084 --> 01:36:21,539
We lost the casino,
we never moved our narcotics...

1163
01:36:21,574 --> 01:36:24,453
...and you're a Irish in a world where there
ain't much of a shortage in guineas.

1164
01:36:24,488 --> 01:36:27,638
Ok, you're walkin' into a building
where he bought up every room.

1165
01:36:28,263 --> 01:36:31,579
I can't hide a weapon. Nothin'.
You're going in blind and we'll be outside.

1166
01:36:34,563 --> 01:36:36,398
Is that enough signs for you?

1167
01:36:41,696 --> 01:36:43,761
I need you to do something for me.

1168
01:36:43,840 --> 01:36:47,052
I need you to go stay in
Miami for just a little while.

1169
01:36:50,310 --> 01:36:52,312
How long is "a little while"?

1170
01:36:52,393 --> 01:36:54,619
I don't know. Not too long.

1171
01:36:55,317 --> 01:36:58,069
I'm not gonna have your address.
I want you give it to Dion.

1172
01:36:58,153 --> 01:37:02,240
When the time comes, he'll tell me
where you are and I'll come get you.

1173
01:37:04,578 --> 01:37:08,371
So you can find out if you are
as cruel as you need to be?

1174
01:37:09,461 --> 01:37:11,211
I guess so.

1175
01:37:12,550 --> 01:37:14,384
Joseph.

1176
01:37:15,133 --> 01:37:20,309
Even if you win today's battle, there
is so much violence in what you do.

1177
01:37:28,196 --> 01:37:29,971
I know.

1178
01:38:33,985 --> 01:38:38,310
Gino, where you livin' now?
In Quonsett. Settlin' down?

1179
01:38:38,899 --> 01:38:42,685
Two kids, hanquera, casa, whole thing.

1180
01:38:42,720 --> 01:38:44,430
Got any?
Not for me.

1181
01:38:45,431 --> 01:38:47,474
There is never a right time.

1182
01:39:11,177 --> 01:39:12,802
This way.

1183
01:39:29,078 --> 01:39:31,317
How are you, my son?

1184
01:39:31,790 --> 01:39:33,337
Fine.

1185
01:39:33,376 --> 01:39:37,661
Fausto, see if Dion needs anything.
Please, come in.

1186
01:39:50,277 --> 01:39:54,033
So, how've you been?
Good. You?

1187
01:39:54,133 --> 01:39:57,430
More good days than bad.
Right.

1188
01:40:01,709 --> 01:40:04,943
This is the filly who fucked
up the whole casino thing?

1189
01:40:05,879 --> 01:40:07,926
Yeah, that's her.

1190
01:40:08,301 --> 01:40:10,530
Why didn't you clip her then?

1191
01:40:11,014 --> 01:40:14,107
Too much blowback.
That's not it.

1192
01:40:15,100 --> 01:40:17,501
You're not a killer, Joseph.

1193
01:40:17,536 --> 01:40:19,822
You are a bandit in a suit.

1194
01:40:19,857 --> 01:40:23,298
That's why you didn't kill that
"puttana pazza."

1195
01:40:23,333 --> 01:40:25,922
You know how much money this
place was doing when I got here?

1196
01:40:25,957 --> 01:40:28,161
You know what it's doing it now?
But that's all rum.

1197
01:40:28,261 --> 01:40:30,166
You neglected the girls
and the narcotics.

1198
01:40:30,250 --> 01:40:32,535
I went after the rum because
it was the most profitable...

1199
01:40:32,540 --> 01:40:34,535
...and I added four houses in my time here

1200
01:40:34,570 --> 01:40:36,225
Yeah, but you could've added more.

1201
01:40:36,260 --> 01:40:39,244
Maso, Look...
Mr. Pescatore!

1202
01:40:41,683 --> 01:40:44,479
I ran Ybor. I ran Tampa.

1203
01:40:44,563 --> 01:40:47,152
Do you ever have a problem?
You did more than that.

1204
01:40:47,252 --> 01:40:49,473
You ran the whole coast.

1205
01:40:49,508 --> 01:40:53,707
You boxed out Albert, put him
in a little piss corner of Miami.

1206
01:40:53,784 --> 01:40:55,826
I've been through the books.

1207
